The <var>PORTDIR</var> variable was<ref>https://gitweb.gentoo.org/proj/pms.git/commit/?id=3abcd75afc8a8ed4400ecd66cc4f129a4bf46330</ref> used to point to the main package repository hosted on the system. It has since been {{Bug|546210|text=deprecated}} in favor of the <code>location</code> attribute (whose default value is {{Path|[[:/usr/portage]]}}) of the Gentoo repository configuration inside {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/repos.conf|/etc/portage/repos.conf]]}}.</onlyinclude>

<!--T:2-->
The current value of the <code>location</code> attribute can be obtained by using [[portageq]]:

<!--T:3-->
{{Cmd|portageq get_repo_path / gentoo|output=<pre>
/usr/portage</pre>}}

